## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-103"><xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule>类是一组.NET Framework 提供了用于管理 Windows 上的命名的系统 mutex 的访问控制安全性的类之一。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-103">The <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> class is one of a set of classes that the .NET Framework provides for managing Windows access control security on named system mutexes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-104">有关这些类和它们与基础 Windows 访问控制结构的关系的概述，请参阅<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-104">For an overview of these classes, and their relationship to the underlying Windows access control structures, see <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="e070d-105">Windows 访问控制安全性是仅对已命名的系统互斥体，有意义。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-105">Windows access control security is meaningful only for named system mutexes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-106">如果<xref:System.Threading.Mutex>对象表示了局部互斥体，则访问控制不起作用。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-106">If a <xref:System.Threading.Mutex> object represents a local mutex, access control is irrelevant.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-107">若要获取当前应用于命名的 mutex 的规则的列表，请使用<xref:System.Threading.Mutex.GetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法以获取<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>对象，以及如何将其<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.CommonObjectSecurity.GetAccessRules%2A>方法来获取一系列<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule>对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-107">To get a list of the rules currently applied to a named mutex, use the <xref:System.Threading.Mutex.GetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method to get a <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity> object, and then use its <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.CommonObjectSecurity.GetAccessRules%2A> method to obtain a collection of <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-108"><xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> 对象不会映射一对一的基础的自由访问控制列表 (DACL) 中的访问控制项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-108"><xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> objects do not map one-to-one with access control entries in the underlying discretionary access control list (DACL).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-109">时的互斥体获取的所有访问规则集，该集合将包含当前表示的访问控制项所需要的规则最小数量。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-109">When you get the set of all access rules for a mutex, the set contains the minimum number of rules currently required to express all the access control entries.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="e070d-110">基础的访问控制项更改，在应用和删除规则。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-110">The underlying access control entries change as you apply and remove rules.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-111">如果可能，合并中规则的信息保持最少数量的访问控制项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-111">The information in rules is merged if possible, to maintain the smallest number of access control entries.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-112">因此，当读取规则的当前列表，它可能不完全一样已添加的所有规则的列表。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-112">Thus, when you read the current list of rules, it might not look exactly like the list of all the rules you have added.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-113">使用<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule>对象来指定要允许或拒绝对用户或组访问权限。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-113">Use <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> objects to specify access rights to allow or deny to a user or group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-114">一个<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule>对象始终表示允许访问还是拒绝访问，但永远不会同时。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-114">A <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> object always represents either allowed access or denied access, never both.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-115">若要将规则应用于已命名的系统互斥体，请使用<xref:System.Threading.Mutex.GetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法以获取<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-115">To apply a rule to a named system mutex, use the <xref:System.Threading.Mutex.GetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method to get the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-116">修改<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>对象使用其方法来添加规则，以及如何将<xref:System.Threading.Mutex.SetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法重新附加的安全对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-116">Modify the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity> object by using its methods to add the rule, and then use the <xref:System.Threading.Mutex.SetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method to reattach the security object.</span></span>  
  
> [!IMPORTANT]
>  <span data-ttu-id="e070d-117">对所做的更改<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>对象并不会影响已命名的 mutex 的访问级别，直到你调用<xref:System.Threading.Mutex.SetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法以将修改过的安全对象分配到命名互斥体。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-117">Changes you make to a <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity> object do not affect the access levels of the named mutex until you call the <xref:System.Threading.Mutex.SetAccessControl%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method to assign the altered security object to the named mutex.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e070d-118"><xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> 对象是不可变。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-118"><xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexAccessRule> objects are immutable.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e070d-119">使用的方法修改的互斥体安全性<xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity>类来添加或删除规则; 执行此操作时，修改基础的访问控制项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-119">Security for a mutex is modified using the methods of the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.MutexSecurity> class to add or remove rules; as you do this, the underlying access control entries are modified.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="e070d-120">Windows 98 或 Windows Millennium Edition 不支持同步对象的安全性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e070d-120">Security on synchronization objects is not supported for Windows 98 or Windows Millennium Edition.</span></span>  
  
   
  
